Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.42,0:06:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Only God knows.\NWe're going to resume the lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.06,0:06:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, my guiding angels are here today, both in and out of body.\NI have permission to ask what I'm going to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.60,0:06:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,My guiding angels are here.\NSo my guiding angels are here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.13,0:07:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So I don't take credit for anything I say.\NSo acknowledging the presence of divinity tends to reinforce when you affirm the presence
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.85,0:07:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of divinity and give thanks to the Lord, you strengthen the guidance that you get from\Nthe Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.99,0:07:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.12,0:07:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo acknowledging...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.10,0:07:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Acknowledging divinity as the source of your existence and thanking God.\NSo giving thanks to God and acknowledging God tends to reinforce the divine energy within
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.76,0:07:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,your own psyche.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.55,0:08:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So even in the pits of hell...\NWhere I was, like, forsaken forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.10,0:08:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it was forever.\NUnbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.14,0:08:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, forever more.\NEternally, you would be cut off from love or salvation forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.63,0:08:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,In the word forever, you got what forever means.\NAnd that was terrifying.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.06,0:08:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.80,0:08:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.75,0:08:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.41,0:08:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.84,0:08:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.98,0:08:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.13,0:08:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.63,0:08:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's when a voice from within me said,\Nif there is a God, I ask him for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.28,0:09:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And then all of hell disappeared\Nand I was suddenly in a radiance
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.48,0:09:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in which the divinity of all that exists\Nshone forth like a radiant light from all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.87,0:09:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That was over 800.\N900.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.21,0:09:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,950.\N945.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.42,0:09:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,950.\NThat moment was 945, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.14,0:09:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,From minus 500 or whatever it was.\NFrom 945's negative to 945's positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.36,0:10:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you're joking.\NThe divinity revealed itself as all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.37,0:10:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NTo know that you are an expression of divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.37,0:10:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,as you.\NYou are an expression of divinity as you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.37,0:10:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I am an expression of divinity as you.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.00,0:10:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So if I can love God,\Nthe beauty of the translator shines forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.54,0:10:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Unmistakable.\NThe beauty of the translator is shown as it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.13,0:10:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no room for misunderstanding.\NThere is no room for misunderstanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.37,0:10:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nyou're very blessed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.26,0:11:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm very blessed to have you today.\NWe are very blessed to have you with us today.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.21,0:11:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And Dr. Moon and all our visitors\Nbecause of them, this occasion arose.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.45,0:11:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And the charm of the Korean people came with you.\NThe charm.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.23,0:11:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The charm.\NThe charm.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.11,0:11:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The charm.\NThe charm.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.28,0:11:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The charm.\NThe charm.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.85,0:11:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The charm.\NThe charm.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.42,0:11:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The charm.\NThe charm.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.11,0:11:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The charm.\NThe charm.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.16,0:11:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, we'll go back to the slides, back to the mundane.\NFrom the sublime to the mundane, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.79,0:11:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, to become educated about the levels of consciousness\Nand the subject of our lectures is a very singular discovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.97,0:12:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, let's see.\NI think this is very interesting,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.90,0:12:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the levels of consciousness and social problems,\Nbecause it's always presumed because of political gain,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.66,0:12:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the political gain,\Nto blame it on society or blame it on a certain culture.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.46,0:12:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's the culture's fault.\NIt's the culture's fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.16,0:12:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if it was the culture's fault,\Nthen everybody who grew up poor would be poor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.28,0:13:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,No, many people grew up poor, and they transcend to that.\NPeople that grew up rich often also become poor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.64,0:13:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So, yeah?\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.76,0:13:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes, I keep forgetting he's there.\NOh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.20,0:13:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He is.\NThe levels of consciousness and the relationships of these things
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.70,0:13:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,are very interesting.\NBecause for political gain,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.98,0:13:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,politicians keep on adding to the causes of culture or certain things.\NBut that doesn't make sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.15,0:13:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why it's very interesting to study this relationship.\NIt's very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.32,0:13:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very interesting.\NIt's very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.55,0:14:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very interesting.\NSo, from this slide, we can stop blaming social conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.34,0:14:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the world is full of political gain\Nby blaming one group for another group, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.17,0:14:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if we study these things,\Nwe can stop adding social responsibility to other things.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.37,0:14:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But all the difficulties,\Nthe social difficulties,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.04,0:14:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the political difficulties,\Ncan be overcome by personal integrity and striving.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.38,0:14:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.37,0:15:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Does anybody have any questions about this level that you see that\Nexperientially what the people are doing is living out their own level of consciousness?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.57,0:15:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NDo you have any questions about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.30,0:15:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What people are experiencing is their own level of consciousness.\NThey are experiencing it as their own level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.57,0:15:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo, and this is why we say that you influence the world by what you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.75,0:15:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what you are, then, is what influences the world,\Nnot by what you do or you say,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.61,0:15:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but by what you do.\NBut by what you become.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.62,0:15:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the best thing we can do for our children, then,\Nis to try to provide for the advancement of their level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.75,0:16:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there's a great benefit to a religious upbringing,\Nspiritual upbringing, spiritual integrus,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.04,0:16:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,whether it's Confucianism or Taoism or Buddhism or Christianity or Hindu,\Nthey all acknowledge a higher power and a gradient of being.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.07,0:16:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That you can become better than you are through endeavor and meditation and service to others.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.99,0:17:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo, like a cork in water, you rise to your own level of buoyancy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.40,0:17:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NSo, to be loving towards all of life in all of its expressions
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.38,0:17:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is the greatest gift you can give to the world.\NSo, when you see the little beetle,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.99,0:17:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I was talking about my little black beetle.\NWhen you see the little black beetle down there in the alley,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.71,0:17:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and you step around the beetle like that,\Nthe world is now a better place than if you went,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.30,0:17:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I always like to talk about this cockroach.\NWhen the cockroach is on the ground,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.98,0:17:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,if you avoid it a little bit,\Nthe world becomes a better place because of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.16,0:18:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather than stepping on it.\NNext slide, Eddie.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.16,0:18:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Next slide, yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.68,0:18:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can tell our students, they always walk over beetles.\NAnybody who's been in these classes, they always step over the beetle.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.59,0:18:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NSo, this is just reading the levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.70,0:18:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and the incidence.\NSo, we'll go to the next one, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.82,0:18:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.21,0:19:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the next section is on spiritual teachers\Nabout which there's a great deal of discussion.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.39,0:19:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The next section is about spiritual teachers.\NBecause of all the books and all the gurus
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.48,0:19:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and the famous and infamous teachers,\Nthe student is often confused which way to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.45,0:19:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the reason that we need to know this is\Nbecause students and students of spiritual books
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.30,0:19:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,are always confused about spiritual teachers.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.91,0:19:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And many questions we get in the mail, you know,\Nasked about a certain teacher, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.02,0:19:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what we try to do is\Nwe publish the list of 100
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.93,0:19:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,integrous teachers over time.\NWe have a list of teachers
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.86,0:19:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that we ask to measure.\NThere are 20 teachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.75,0:20:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And what level of, what is the level of their teaching, say, what is the level of their teaching?\NSo, a higher number doesn't necessarily mean that that teacher is better for you right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.83,0:20:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Because a teacher who calibrates at 500 would be better for you than a teacher who calibrates at 800, but you don't understand anything he's saying.\NAlright, so we wanted to print out,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.98,0:21:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,what are the characteristics that define the excellence of a teacher,\Nso that the student can become independent of the calibrated levels that they can learn for themselves?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.35,0:21:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NAlright, so we say that truth is not limited to the possession of only certain teachers or people, that it's really open to everyone. Truth is all-inclusive.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.50,0:21:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is not a possession of one particular teacher, and that it contains everything.\NAnd that it is available to everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.24,0:22:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, so truth is all-inclusive, and it's not given out as a secret.\NAnd it's non-sectarian.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.13,0:22:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not the exclusive property of any one religion or spiritual pathway.\NSo there are great teachers in all the world's bona fide religions.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.15,0:22:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The great teachers can be of any religion.\NSo there are great teachers in all the world's bona fide religions.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.50,0:23:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,No secrets to be revealed, hidden, sold, magical formulas or mysteries.\NPeople say for $10,000, I will tell you,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.92,0:23:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,there are no secrets to be revealed, hidden, sold, magical formulas or mysteries.\NPeople say for $10,000, I will tell you,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.51,0:23:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,there are no secrets to be revealed, hidden, sold, magical formulas or mysteries.\NThere are no secrets to be revealed, hidden, sold, magical formulas or mysteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.74,0:23:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So, availability.\NOpen to all.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.35,0:23:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-exclusive.\NNo secrets to be revealed, hidden, or sold, magical formulas, so.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.93,0:24:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,There are teachers out there that for $5,000 will tell you the secrets.\NThere are teachers out there that for $5,000 will tell you the secrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.74,0:24:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll do it for $4,000.\NI'll do it for $4,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.08,0:24:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll buy it.\NThey say they'll do it for $4,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.70,0:24:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So then, you need compassion for the teacher,\Nwho is not fully developed as a teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.20,0:24:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you pray for the teacher that will reach full enlightenment.\NSo, you need compassion for the teacher that will reach full enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.40,0:24:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo, a true teacher,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.03,0:24:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So, a true teacher, there is,\Nnothing to gain or lose
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.13,0:25:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no profit\Nno gain or loss
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.47,0:25:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,if you think he's great\Nthat's fine
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.43,0:25:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you don't think\Nhe's great that's fine
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.09,0:25:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,because the spiritual\Nego is the only thing that would make you
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.75,0:25:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,create fame and fortune\Nand to be famous
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.10,0:25:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and all over the world\Nbecause
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.18,0:25:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,only the spiritual ego\Nis trying to become famous
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.00,0:25:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and want to be praised\Nto a true teacher
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.89,0:25:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,there's nothing to gain or lose\Nbecause
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.07,0:25:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that which you know\Nwith the capital
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.05,0:26:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,capital K\Nis beyond approval
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.05,0:26:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,disapproval\Nagreement
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.46,0:26:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,disagreement\Nmoney
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.85,0:26:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,fame\Nall those things are foolish
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.96,0:26:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,because what you know\Nis beyond profit and honor
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.70,0:26:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,alright\Nwe have a lot of things that define truth here
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.93,0:26:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it's independent of opinion\Nindependent of opinion
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.48,0:26:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,so\Nyou know I got to get
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.81,0:26:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,ourself emails of people's various opinions\Nand I don't pay any attention to them
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.18,0:26:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,because\Nthey're not talking about anything having to do with truth or reality
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.88,0:26:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,they're talking about their own perception\Nand perception
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.88,0:26:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is not of any particular interest\Nthe truth has nothing to do with opinions
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.51,0:27:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,so I get a lot of emails from many people\Nbut I don't care about that at all
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.51,0:27:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,they only care about their opinions and opinions so I don't care about that at all\Nso I don't care about that at all
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.85,0:27:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,they're only talking about their own perception\Nyeah see truth is independent of opinion
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.18,0:27:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not anti-anything\Nand falsehood is not its enemy
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.00,0:27:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but really the absence of truth\Nso truth is either present or not present
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.00,0:27:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so truth has to do with opinion\Nthe truth is either present or not present
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.00,0:27:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,so truth has to do with opinion\Ntruth has to do with the essence of things
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.35,0:27:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,falsehood has to do with perception of things\Ntruth has to do with the essence of things
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.35,0:27:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,falsehood has to do with perception of things\Nnow to convey the truth or to teach the truth or to make it available
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.99,0:28:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,there are no required memberships or dues\Nthere's no regulations
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.45,0:28:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to dress in some funny way\Nyou don't have to take any oaths
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.93,0:28:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no rules\Nno conditions
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.00,0:28:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and you don't\Nthere's no conditions, no oaths, no rules
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.00,0:28:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,no requirements, no demands\Nto make truth available
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.24,0:28:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to demand anything\Nyou don't have to make any rules
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.24,0:28:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to make any conditions\Nyou don't have to make any conditions
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.24,0:28:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that sounds pretty good doesn't it\NI'll go for that
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.00,0:28:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go for that\NI'll go for that
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.00,0:28:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go for that\Nokay
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.09,0:28:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,no requirement, no regulations\Nno oaths, no rules
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.39,0:28:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,no conditions\Nto know the truth then is volitional only
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.96,0:29:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing is required\Nall right
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.75,0:29:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,so the conveyor of truth is non-controlling\Nnot interested in controlling people
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.83,0:29:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual purity has no interest\Nin the personal lives of students
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.11,0:29:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the conveyor of truth is not interested in control\Nand spiritual purity is not interested in the personal lives of students
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.64,0:29:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,now in Sedona we had a spiritual teacher\Nwho is now left
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.89,0:29:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,but it was the exact opposite of this\Ntold everybody what they must do
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.89,0:29:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,who they could go to bed with\Nwho they could ride in a car with
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.89,0:29:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to give them the money\Nsign over all their property to him
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.89,0:30:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,now there is no one in Sedona\Nwho is against this at all
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.89,0:30:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,who has to sleep with someone\Nwho has to wear certain clothes
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.89,0:30:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,who has to drive certain cars\Nhe controlled all of this
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.89,0:30:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah\Nwhat you should eat
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.89,0:30:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,what you should dress\Nall about your sex life
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.89,0:30:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,all about your money\Nwhat your family should do
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.89,0:30:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,what kind of car you should drive in\Nnow what in the world would anybody who is spiritually advanced care about all that
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.89,0:30:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,all right\Nso
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.36,0:30:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,two spiritual teachings are free of force or intimidation\Nno force or intimidation
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.72,0:30:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,no brainwashing\Nworship of the leader
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.28,0:30:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,indoctrination\Nrituals
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.08,0:31:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,intrusions into private life\Nso the true spiritual teacher then
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.64,0:31:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,teaches by content\Nwhat we talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.35,0:31:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,but teaches primarily by the radiation\Nof the energy field of that
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.86,0:31:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,which the teacher is in truth.\N영적인 스승은
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.84,0:31:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,내용으로도 가리키지만\N1차적으로는
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.50,0:31:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,그가 방사하는 영적인 에너지로서\N가르침을 펼칩니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.30,0:31:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes through as a radiation\Nfrom the aura of the teacher
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.23,0:31:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to the aura of the student.\N그의 가르침은
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.32,0:31:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,스승의 오라로부터\N학생의 오라로 전달됩니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.84,0:31:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,광이로서 전달됩니다.\NAnd the aura does not belong to the teacher
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.02,0:32:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,그 오라는 스승에게\N귀속되지 않습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.82,0:32:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that energy that the teacher has\Ncame from his teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.75,0:32:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,왜냐하면\N그 스승이 가진 에너지는
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.01,0:32:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,그 스승의 스승에게로부터\N왔기 때문입니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.20,0:32:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That which radiates forth\Nfrom the consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.03,0:32:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of the teacher\Nwas already a gift to the teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.11,0:32:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,그의 의식에서\N발현되는 그것은
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.61,0:32:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,이미 다른 스승으로부터의\N선물이었습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.66,0:32:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So the teacher\Nout of humility
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.23,0:32:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,is grateful\Nthat he has been allowed
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.41,0:32:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to serve such a function.\N그러므로
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.43,0:32:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,겸손함을 가지고\N그 스승은
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.36,0:32:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,이제 스승의 역할을\N할 수 있다는 것에 대해서
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.99,0:32:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,감사하게 여깁니다.\NSo it creates
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.00,0:32:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,greater humility\Nrather than
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.27,0:32:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,magnifying the ego.\NYou say,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.24,0:32:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear Lord,\NI give thanks to Thee
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.20,0:32:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that I have been assigned\Nthis mission
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.93,0:33:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,by which I may serve Thee\Nand my fellow men.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.78,0:33:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen.\N이러한 것에 대한 이해는
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.84,0:33:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,애고를 강화시키는 것 대신\N겸손함을 강화시키고
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.80,0:33:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,제가 당신의 가르침을\N제 동료 인간에게
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.86,0:33:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,전달할 수 있게 되신 것에 대해서\N신에게 감사를 드리게 됩니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.06,0:33:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NSo then,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.45,0:33:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you become\Nthe teacher becomes
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.42,0:33:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,aligned with serving\NGod and his fellow man
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.85,0:33:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,serving others\Nby virtue of that
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.96,0:33:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,what he has become\Nto be that.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.98,0:33:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,자신이 된 그것으로서\N신과 동료 인간과
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.93,0:33:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,정렬되게 됩니다.\N가르침으로서 정렬시켜줍니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.13,0:33:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.30,0:33:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So the next slide.\NI can't read anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.85,0:33:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, non-binding.\NI remember when I was young,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.79,0:33:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I was invited to become\Na member of a certain group
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.74,0:34:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and I found out\Nthat you had to take an oath.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.81,0:34:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,제가 어릴 때\N어떤 사람들과 어울리기 위해서
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.66,0:34:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,그들 외에 멤버가 되기 위해서는\N어떤 선서를 해야 된다는 것을
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.21,0:34:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,알게 되었습니다.\NAnd yet, at age 12,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.09,0:34:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I was 12,\N열두 살 때였는데요.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.07,0:34:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew better than to take an oath.\N저는 그 선서를 해서는
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.76,0:34:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,안 된다는 것을 알았습니다.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.40,0:34:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So I can discuss,\NI can reveal this result.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.28,0:34:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,이것에 대해서\NIs it okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.61,0:34:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NAlright.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.15,0:34:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Because oaths are binding\Nfrom one lifetime to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.90,0:34:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,왜냐하면 선서를 하지 않아야 하는 것은\N선서는 생을 거듭해서
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.07,0:34:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,그 사람을 묶기 때문입니다.\NSo a true teacher wants you to be free
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.28,0:34:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and not bound.\N진정한 스승은 당신이
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.69,0:34:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,자유롭기를 원하지\N묶이기를 원하지 않습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.11,0:34:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, therefore,\Nstudents are free to come and go
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.90,0:35:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,without trying to persuade them,\Ncoerce them, threaten them,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.30,0:35:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,intimidate them,\Nexcommunicate them,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.15,0:35:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,tax them,\Nor chop their heads off.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.13,0:35:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,그렇기 때문에\N스승은 학생들이 자유롭게 오가길 원합니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.42,0:35:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,설득하지도 않고,\N강제력을 행사하지도 않고,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.92,0:35:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,겁을 주지도 않고,\N세금을 매기지도 않고,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.28,0:35:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,머리를 잘라버리지도 않습니다.\NThere are people who make converts
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.88,0:35:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,by giving you your choice,\Nto either join them
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.69,0:35:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,or become beheaded.\N그 스승을 따르게 되는 사람 중에는
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.46,0:35:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,여기 들어오든지,\N아니면 머리가 잘리든지의 선택권에서
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.53,0:35:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,그렇게 결정한 사람들도 있습니다.\NSo, real integrity allows for freedom,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.13,0:35:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,allows you to say yes or no\Nwithout any consequences.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.59,0:35:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And if a person declines,\Nthen the proper thing for the teacher
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.98,0:36:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,is to pray for that person's enlightenment.\N그래서 진정한 스승은 자유를 허락하고
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.73,0:36:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,그에게 yes나 no를 선택할 기회를 주고\N그들이 만약 거부한다면
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.42,0:36:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,그들을 위해서\N그들이 알만한 적당한 길을 선택하도록 기도해 줍니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.80,0:36:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo the teacher is inspirational.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.86,0:36:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth avoids glamorization, seduction,\Nand theatrics.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.09,0:36:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,진실은 영감을 고치시키고\N어떤 유혹하는 것이나
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.76,0:36:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,그 다음에 어떤 과시하는 것\N이런 것을 모두 피합니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.63,0:36:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is devoid of neediness of worldly wealth,\Nprestige, titles, pomp, edifices.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.88,0:37:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,진실은 세상적인 부와\N명성과 어떤 거대한 구조물
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.86,0:37:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,이런 것들을 모두 필요로 하지 않습니다.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.92,0:37:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So truth stands on its own.\N진실은 그 자체로 섭니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.03,0:37:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Without formalities, theatrics, drum and bugle,\Norchestras, and dancing girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.23,0:37:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,진실은 어떤 과대 포장이라든지\N오케스트라 뮤직이라든지
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.13,0:37:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,아니면 춤추는 여인들 없이도\N스스로 그 자체로서 섭니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.98,0:37:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think in its higher form\Nit also avoids extremes of asceticism.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.00,0:37:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,그리고 또 한 가지는\N어떤 극단주의적인 금욕주의도 거부합니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.38,0:37:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that occurs in the Hindu tradition.\N그것은
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.67,0:37:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAsceticism to an extreme degree
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.13,0:37:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,where you're profoundly emaciated\Nand falling over from hunger and weakness
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.40,0:37:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is not a necessity.\NI think.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.13,0:38:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,힌두 전통에서 발생한\N아주 극단주의적인 어떤 금욕주의
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.96,0:38:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,배고픔으로 인해서 바짝 말라서 쓰러지는\N그러한 것은 결코 필요하지 않습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.05,0:38:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth itself fulfilling and complete.\NIt is already total and complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.30,0:38:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Has no need to proselytize,\Ngain adherence, sign up members, followers,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.67,0:38:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,send in dues.\N진실은 자기 전통에서
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.67,0:38:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,충족적이며\N이미 완전하고
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.88,0:38:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,완전 무결하기 때문에\N전도할 필요도 없고
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.26,0:38:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,추종자들을 얻으려고 노력하거나\N멤버들을 이렇게
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.15,0:38:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,사인업 시키지도 않습니다.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.07,0:38:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Now,\Nthere is non-involvement in worldly affairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.09,0:38:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're in the world\Nbut not of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.01,0:39:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NI'm in the world but not of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.78,0:39:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,세상에 있기지만 세상적이지는 않습니다.\NThe world is as it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.23,0:39:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is as it is.\N있는 그대로 있을 뿐입니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.65,0:39:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's no need to control others.\NYou see how much of the conflicts of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.46,0:39:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,are due to one group or person trying to control others.\NIf I think this way, you have to think this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.92,0:39:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Seeking agreement.\NWhy does the world seek agreement?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.61,0:39:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\N세상에 많은 문제는
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.71,0:39:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,누군가를 통제하려고 하는 것 때문에 일어납니다.\N모두 자신이 하고자 하는 것에
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.65,0:39:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,동의를 구하려고 하기 때문에\N이러한 폭력들이 발생합니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.30,0:40:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to think the way they think.\NWhy is it people insist that you think the way they must think?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.57,0:40:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,우리는 상대방이 생각하는 대로 생각하도록 강요받습니다.\N왜 우리가 그래야 할까요?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.73,0:40:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so you can believe in Christmas or not.\N당신은 크리스마스를 믿어도 되고 믿지 않아도 됩니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.07,0:40:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,If I believe in Christmas, you don't have to.\N제가 크리스마스를 믿는다고 해서 당신이 꼭 그래야 할 필요는 없습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.86,0:40:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NIf I don't believe in Christmas, you don't have to stop believing in Christmas
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.42,0:40:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,because I don't believe in Christmas.\N제가 크리스마스를 믿지 않는다고 해서
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.86,0:40:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,당신이 크리스마스를 믿는 것을 그만둬야 할 필요도 없습니다.\NSo you see how interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.61,0:40:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The daily news is when you see it goes back and forth\Nfor these groups trying to force other people
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.88,0:40:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to think and see and perceive the way they do.\N그래서 이러한 것을 이해하게 되면
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.67,0:40:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,우리가 매일 신문에서 보는 것처럼\N다른 사람이 자기가 생각하는 대로
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.34,0:40:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,자신이 지각하는 대로\N자신이 믿는 대로 다른 사람들에게 강요하는 것이
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.96,0:41:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,얼마나 우습다는 것을 알 수 있습니다.\NNow you say, why is the human that way?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.80,0:41:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That he wants everybody to agree with him.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.67,0:41:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,인간은 다른 사람들이 자신과 똑같이\N생각하고 행동하기를 원하는 것일까요?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.13,0:41:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Why must everybody agree with you?\N왜 모든 사람이 당신에게 동의해야 합니까?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.76,0:41:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So the core of that which is anti-God\Nand anti-freedom
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.90,0:41:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is the narcissistic core of the ego.\N신에게 부정적인 것의 핵심은
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.71,0:41:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,자기애적인 애고의 애고입니다.\NEverybody has...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.78,0:41:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He has to see it my way.\N모든 사람들이 내가 보는 것처럼 봐야 되죠.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.50,0:41:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I am right and you are wrong.\N왜냐하면 내가 옳고 당신은 그르기 때문입니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.92,0:41:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's egotism.\N이러한 것이 바로 자기중심주의입니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.71,0:42:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So the opposite of God, the enemy of God\Nis the narcissistic core of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.65,0:42:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,그렇기 때문에 신에게 반대하는 것\N그리고 신에게 반대하는 것이
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.28,0:42:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,신에게 대항하는 것은\N자기애적인 애고의 핵심입니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.32,0:42:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So the core of the ego is me, me, me, me, me.\N그래서 애고의 핵심은
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.73,0:42:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,나, 나, 나를 찾는 바로 그것입니다.\NYeah, me, me, me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.15,0:42:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Vote for me.\NBuy me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.30,0:42:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Photograph me.\NWorship me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.92,0:42:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Send your money.\NSend your emails.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.32,0:42:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Send your...\NThat machine that they talk on.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.76,0:42:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Blogs.\NSend me your blogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.78,0:42:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,블로그도 좀 보내주시고.\NThe world is suffocating with blogism.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.40,0:42:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,세상은 지금 블로그리즘에 의해서 아주 숨막힐 지경입니다.\NSo all that people do when they make an utterance
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.13,0:43:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,is a verbalized blog.\N그래서 어떤 사람이 무언가를 얘기할 때
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.11,0:43:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean blog?\N블로그.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.01,0:43:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Blog.\NBlog.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.65,0:43:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,사람들이 말할 때 블로그리즘.\N블로그리즘.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.21,0:43:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,우리가 블로그로 하는 그런 것들이 언어와되고 있는 것이나 마찬가지입니다.\NSo when you boil it down,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.50,0:43:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,there's only God and blogs.\N그래서 이것을 바닥까지 들여다보게 되면
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.40,0:43:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,신과 블로그만 남게 됩니다.\NNow, God doesn't know how to work a computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.61,0:43:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,그런데 신은 컴퓨터를 사용할지 모릅니다.\NHe doesn't know how to text.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.96,0:43:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't know how to text.\NHe doesn't know how to text.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.11,0:43:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't know how to text.\NHe doesn't know how to text.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.21,0:43:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't know how to text.\NHe doesn't know how to text.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.28,0:43:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't know how to text.\NHe doesn't know how to text.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.36,0:43:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't know how to text.\NHe doesn't know how to text.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.46,0:43:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't know how to text.\N문자를 보낼 수 있는 능력이 없습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.44,0:44:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So you break the world, the tragedies of the world down,\Nand you begin to see them as humor and absurdity.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.76,0:44:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,세상의 문제들을 이렇게 차근차근 나열해 보게 되면\N거기서 휴머를 보게 되고 이것이 부조리하다는 것을 알게 됩니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.84,0:44:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So then there is only knowing the truth and ignorance.\N그렇기 때문에 결국에는
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.53,0:44:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,진실을 아는 것과 무지만이 남게 됩니다.\NSo Jesus Christ said that there is only one source of sin
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.46,0:44:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and there is only one sin and that is of ignorance.\N그래서 예수님께서는 죄의 근원은 단 하나이고
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.44,0:44:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,그것은 무지라고 말했습니다.\NThere is only ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.01,0:44:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,오로지 무지만이 있을 뿐입니다.\NAnd that which we consider evil and all that is all profound ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.09,0:45:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,그래서 우리가 악마라고 여기는 그러한 것들은\N사실은 아주 심온한 무지일 뿐입니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.84,0:45:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddha said the same thing.\N부처님도 같은 말씀을 하셨습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.73,0:45:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Krishna said the same thing.\NI say the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.90,0:45:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,박사님도 같은 말씀을 하셨습니다.\NA lot of them out there are just plain stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.71,0:45:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,세상에 많은 사람들은 그냥 어리석은 짓을 하고 있을 뿐입니다.\NThe karmically earn the right to hear the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.59,0:45:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and be exposed to the truth\Njust as one karmically evolves to the place
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.75,0:46:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that they can comprehend the truth and recognize the truth.\N진실을 배우고 진실에 노출되기 위해서
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.53,0:46:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,사람은 카르마적으로 그것을 획득해야 됩니다.\NSo the Buddha said many can listen but few can hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.92,0:46:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,그래서 부처님은 많은 사람들이 진실을\N들을 수는 있지만 진정으로
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.30,0:46:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,들은 사람들은 적다고 말했습니다.\NMany listen but few can hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.07,0:46:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,많은 사람들이 들을 수는 있으나\N아주 소수만이 이해할 수 있다고 했습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.46,0:46:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Buddha spoke to those who are able to hear.\NTo those who can hear, he spoke the Buddha.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.86,0:46:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddha spoke to those who can hear.\N부처님은 들을 수 있는 사람들은
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.94,0:46:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,이해할 수 있는 사람들에게 말했습니다.\NSo a wise prayer is to pray to be able to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.46,0:47:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,그래서 현명한 기도는 이해할 수 있도록 해달라고 기도하는 것입니다.\NAnd then your guiding angels get your willingness
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.19,0:47:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and see to it that you come into the presence of a teacher\Nwho will explain what you need to know
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.69,0:47:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and willing to know and able to grasp.\N그렇게 기도하게 되면 당신의 안내를
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.50,0:47:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,당신의 안내를 알 수 있습니다.\N당신의 안내 천사가 당신이
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.15,0:47:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,그것을 진실을 이해할 수 있고\N듣고 이해할 수 있도록 전달해 줄 수 있는
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.86,0:47:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,스승의 현존에 있게끔 해줍니다.\NYeah, so the Buddha was a great teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.48,0:47:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He spoke from wisdom.\N부처는 지혜로부터 지혜의 말씀을 하신
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.92,0:47:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,훌륭한 스승이었습니다.\NHe said, let those who can hear, hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.15,0:47:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,들을 수 있는 자만이 이해할 수 있는 사람들에게\N들을 수 있는 자만이 이해할 수 있는 사람들에게
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.19,0:47:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,들을 수 있는 자만이 듣도록 들어라.\N라고 말했습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.76,0:48:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Let those who can hear, hear.\NI like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.42,0:48:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,들을 수 있는 자만이 들어라.\NUh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.76,0:48:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,호케스 밥스님이 좋아하시는 겁니다.\NThen you're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.59,0:48:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that's non-controlling, you know.\NAnd he's acknowledging that your capacity to hear
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.84,0:48:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,is considerably your own karmic inheritance.\NYou may not be able to hear, and it's not your fault
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.15,0:48:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,because at this point you cannot hear yet.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.98,0:48:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,왜냐하면 그러한 것은 통제하는 것이 아니니까요.\N왜냐하면 그러한 것은 통제하는 것이 아니니까요.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.82,0:48:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,부처님께서는 당신이 들을 수 있는 능력은\N당신의 카르마적인 어떤 자산이라는 것을
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.53,0:48:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,인정하셨습니다.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.59,0:48:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So, truth then tries to inspire and lead people\Nto the truth or to the conditions that allow you
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.01,0:48:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to hear the truth.\NSo that's why humility is constantly stressed
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.46,0:48:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,in all spiritual teachings.\NHumility, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.94,0:48:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.\NUh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.44,0:49:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,진실은, uh-huh.\N진실은 당신에게, 당신이 그것을 이해할 수 있는 조건들을
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.34,0:49:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,허락해 주기 때문에, 그래서 겸손함이라는 것이\N계속해서 강조되는 이유입니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.40,0:49:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So truth does not seek to control others.\N진실은 다른 이들을 통제하려 하지 않습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.84,0:49:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't want to have to convince others or force others.\N진실은 다른 사람을 확신시키려고 하지도 않고
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.51,0:49:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,진실은 다른 사람을 확신시키려고 하지도 않고\N강제하지도 않습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.53,0:49:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You will go to the next slide.\NAnd, uh, there are no issues or positionalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.15,0:49:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,어떤 문제도 없고 위치성도 있지 않습니다.\NGod doesn't need help.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.03,0:49:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,신은 도움을 필요로 하지 않습니다.\NPeople, I think, they're helping God.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.94,0:50:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I will, if you don't believe the way I believe,\NI'll cut your head off.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.21,0:50:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And he thinks that way you're helping God.\NSo we have to become humble and realize
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.32,0:50:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,God doesn't need your help.\N그렇기 때문에 우리는 신이 우리의 도움을 필요로 하지 않는다는 것을
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.94,0:50:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,느끼고 겸손해져야 합니다.\NGod's made it this far without your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.96,0:50:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,신은 당신의 도움 없이도 이렇게 훌륭하십니다.\NYeah, so the more sophisticated,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.59,0:50:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,we become, we become aware that\Ndivinity is like an infinite source of energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.46,0:50:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,infinitely powerful source of energy,\Nand that within that field,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.09,0:51:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you are free to move about or come or go.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.71,0:51:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,우리가 점점 더 진보함에 따라서 우리는 신성이라고 하는 것이\N에너지의 무한한 근원이라는 것을 이해하고
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.38,0:51:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,그 안에서 우리는 자유롭게 움직일 수 있습니다.\NAll right, so that which all spiritual truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.51,0:51:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite spiritual truth is beyond proof.\N모든 영적인 진실은 증명을 넘어서 있습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.61,0:51:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is provable is within the linear domain,\Nthe Newtonian domain.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.86,0:51:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,증명할 수 있는 것은 선형적인 뉴톤적 영역에 속하는 것입니다.\NAll right, that which is provable,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.67,0:51:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is obviously not divine.\N그렇기 때문에 분명히 증명할 수 있는 것은 신성한 것이 아닙니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.03,0:52:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way you can prove the infinite.\N무한을 증명할 수 있는 방법은 존재하지 않습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.13,0:52:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Many of the journals having to do with religion and things\Ncalibrate in the 300s.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.53,0:52:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all about theology and God and all this.\NWhen you calibrate them,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.48,0:52:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,they're like in the 300s.\NSo what they're talking about is not the reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.84,0:52:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,but intellectualizations about the reality.\N종교나 그러한 신학에 관한 그러한 학술 잡지들은
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.15,0:52:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,측정을 해본다면 300대로 측정됩니다.\N이 사실이 말하는 것은 그들은 신성이라고 하는 것을
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.05,0:52:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,실상이 아닌 단지 주지화하고 있는 것입니다.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.57,0:52:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this one is...\NOne of the basics to know that is that life is not subject to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.17,0:53:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, there's the law of the preservation of energy.\NEnergy cannot be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.03,0:53:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It can only change form.\NMatter cannot be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.46,0:53:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It can only change form.\N알아야 하실 아주 기본적인 것은 생명이 파괴될 수 없다는 것입니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.09,0:53:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,진량 보존의 법칙과 에너지 법칙,\N보존의 법칙이 있듯이 에너지가 오로지 형상만을 바꿀 수 있듯이 생명도 그러합니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.50,0:53:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NNow, more recently discovered is the third principle.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.98,0:53:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That is, the truth cannot be, life cannot be destroyed.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.61,0:53:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Life cannot be destroyed.\NSo matter cannot be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.96,0:53:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Energy cannot be destroyed.\NAnd now, the third great discovery is that,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.48,0:54:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that life cannot be destroyed.\NMaterial can only change form from one form to another.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.42,0:54:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Energy can only change from one form to another,\Nbut you cannot destroy energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.61,0:54:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,생명이...\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.96,0:54:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, oh, I forgot about it.\N에너지가 소멸될 수 없고, 진량이, 물질이 소멸될 수 없듯이,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.07,0:54:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,세 번째 위대한 발견은 생명도 파괴될 수 없다는 것입니다.\NSo we're all familiar with the basic concept that matter cannot be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.86,0:54:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It can only change form.\N우리는 모두 물질이 파괴될 수 없고, 단지 형태만을 바꿀 수 있다는 것을 잘 알고 있습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.44,0:54:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And energy cannot be destroyed.\NIt can only change form.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.07,0:55:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,에너지도 파괴될 수 없고, 오로지 형상만을 바꿀 수 있습니다.\NAnd now, a third discovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.98,0:55:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,세 번째,\N세 번째 발견입니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.90,0:55:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The third discovery.\NWhat is the third discovery again?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.51,0:55:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Life cannot be destroyed.\NIt can only change form.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.44,0:55:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,세 번째 발견은 생명도 파괴될 수 없고, 단지 형상만을 바꿀 수 있을 뿐입니다.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.86,0:55:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So, known before was that matter and energy cannot be destroyed.\NBut nowhere have I ever read that life cannot be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.90,0:55:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,이전에 에너지와 물질이,\N에너지와 물질이,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.86,0:55:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,파괴될 수 없다는 것은 모두 알고 있었지만,\N누구도 생명이 파괴될 수 없고, 오로지 형상만을 바꿀 수 있다는 것은 들어본 적이 없을 것입니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.88,0:55:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright. Like matter and energy,\Nlife can only change form, but you cannot destroy life.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.61,0:56:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Life cannot be destroyed.\N에너지와 물질과 마찬가지로 생명은 파괴될 수 없고, 오로지 형상만을 바꿀 수 있습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.34,0:56:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Life cannot be destroyed. Resist.\NIt can only change form.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.80,0:56:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nthe only thing that can happen if they chop off your head is that you leave your physical body and there you are in your etheric body.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.46,0:56:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,그렇기 때문에, 누군가 당신의 머리를 잘라낸다면, 육체성은 사라지지만, 당신은 이제 이 에테르체에 있게 됩니다.\NSo, I've been in my physical body and thought that's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.01,0:56:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,저는 육체 없이 에테르체에 있었습니다.\N있어본 적이 있습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.63,0:56:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I've been out of my body.\N저는 육체를 벗어난 적도 있습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.84,0:56:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And the body was over there.\N육체는 저기에 있었고.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.84,0:56:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And consciousness says, this is me.\N의식은, 이게 나다 라고 말했습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.36,0:56:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the body is there and me is here. How can that be?\N육체는 저기 있고, 저는 여기 있고. 이것이 어떻게 가능할까요?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.28,0:57:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you also have an etheric body.\N왜냐하면 당신은 또한 에테르체도 가지고 있기 때문입니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.53,0:57:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The spirit, the soul, that which leaves the body at the point of death, yeah.\N영과 영혼은 육신이 죽을 때 몸을 떠납니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.53,0:57:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So, a third great teaching is that life cannot be destroyed, it can only change form.\N그러므로 세 번째 위대한 가르침은, 생명은 파괴될 수 없고 오로지 형상만을 바꿀 수 있다는 것입니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.21,0:57:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true at the level of the absolute resist.\NThat is true at the level of the absolute, life cannot be destroyed, it can only change form.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.63,0:57:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that good news?\N좋은 소식 아닌가요?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.19,0:57:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't like being a human being, you can come back. Hop, hop, hop, bunny, bunny. Hop, hop, bunny, bunny.\N사람이 되기 싫으면 말로 태어나실 수도 있습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.36,0:58:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,새로 태어나실 수도 있고요.\NI thought it would be great to be an eagle. Go up a mile in the sky, and ten miles away you can spot a mouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.28,0:58:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, that must be something.\N독수리가 된다는 것은 굉장히 멋질 거라고 생각했습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.28,0:58:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,한 천 미터도 넘게 올라가서 쥐를 볼 수 있는 능력을 갖는다.\NYou don't even need glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.28,0:58:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,안경도 필요 없습니다.\NThe eagle, miles away, can spot a mouse from over a thousand feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.07,0:58:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's see. I think that's the last of the slides, and then we're going to go on to more interesting things.\NI don't know what they are, but that's what they say.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.82,0:58:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the end of this?\NOh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.07,0:59:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Simplicity.\NOne sees the intrinsic beauty of that which is beyond appearance and form.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.57,0:59:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in a moment of mystical revelation, the overwhelming beauty of what exists, you're knocked out by the beauty, beauty.\N그렇기 때문에
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.76,0:59:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,압도적인 드러남의 상태에서 모든 것에 내지 않은 본질적인 아름다움이 당신을 쓰러트려 버립니다.\NTruth does not do anything. It just is.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.19,0:59:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And its influence is as a consequence of that which it is.\N진실은 어떤 것도 하지 않으며, 모든 것을 그저 그것의 존재로서 영향을 미칩니다. 모든 것에.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.63,0:59:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NAnd truth is not emotional.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.63,0:59:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Emotionality is based on perception.\N진실은 감정적이지 않습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.44,1:00:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,감정성이라는 것은 지각에 근거한 것입니다.\NTruth is sought, is found through freedom, rather than rules and restrictions.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.96,1:00:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,진실은 자유를 통해서 따르게 되며, 따르게 되지, 룰이나 이런 것으로 인해서 지켜지지 않습니다.\NAnd true spiritual teachers are respected,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.78,1:00:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,but they reject personal adulation or specialness.\N진정한 스승은 존경되기는 하나, 개인적인 찬양은 거절합니다.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.84,1:00:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The recognition of truth is natural.\NIt's devoid of induced, altered states of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.84,1:00:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,various manipulating energies up and down the spine,\Nand magical breathing,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.00,1:00:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and the power of the mind.\NLet's do this one.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.78,1:01:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That calibrates over 190, 195.\NThink of those students all over the planet doing,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.01,1:01:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 190.\NYou're dumber than when you started it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.23,1:01:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,이 호흡법은 195로 측정되며, 이걸 하게 되면 당신이 시작하기 전보다 더 어리석게 되죠.\NSo, alright, we're almost done.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.19,1:01:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's wise then,\Nto really check out the integrity of a teacher,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.61,1:01:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,a teaching, a method,\Nthe fact that it's called yoga.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.61,1:01:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's yoga.\NI'll give you a yoga.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.96,1:01:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Try this yoga.\NTry that yoga.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.17,1:01:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Try this yoga.\NThe fact that it's called a yoga,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.32,1:02:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a mystical, magical,\Nbetter than butter is yoga.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.76,1:02:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yoga spread.\NYoga talks.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.38,1:02:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yoga socks.\NYoga shoes.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.73,1:02:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yoga flowers.\NOkay, I'll do all over.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.15,1:02:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.63,1:02:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It was my pleasure.\NThank you for being our translator.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.63,1:03:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And tell the people what are we going to do.\NI don't know what we're going to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.00,1:03:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to take a 15-minute break here.\NAnd anyone who has a question,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.00,1:03:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,if they will please line up on this side.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.00,1:03:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The auditorium.\NAnyone who needs book signing,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.00,1:03:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we did sign a lot of the books.\NBut if you want something signed,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.00,1:03:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,take it to this side of the auditorium.\NAnd we'll resume in about 15 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.00,1:03:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We're a little bit over,\Nso we'll probably run over a little bit in the break.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.00,1:03:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But we're a little bit over.\NAnd this lady over here that's in the Korean costume,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.00,1:03:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,come here.\NThis is typical of the Korean dress.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.00,1:03:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so beautiful.\NAnd I wanted all of you to take a look.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.00,1:03:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Take a good look at it.\NCome here.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.84,1:03:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I want them to see your dress.\NA lot of the people here in the U.S.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.84,1:03:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,haven't seen the traditional Korean.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.84,1:03:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your playing.\NIsn't that beautiful?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.84,1:04:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.21,1:04:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NWe'll resume in about 15 minutes then.
